(Fu's Moo-Moo)

278
00:18:59,182 --> 00:19:00,342
How can it be normal

279
00:19:00,802 --> 00:19:02,502
when you're someone so special to me?

280
00:19:06,403 --> 00:19:07,073
Moo,

281
00:19:07,322 --> 00:19:08,382
you do realize

282
00:19:08,937 --> 00:19:11,024
that not everyone on Earth

283
00:19:16,032 --> 00:19:19,182
can be as good on the inside
as they are on the outside like I am.

284
00:19:19,982 --> 00:19:22,742
Plus, there's no one who has
better intention toward you than I am...

285
00:19:22,782 --> 00:19:23,582
Enough.

286
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:25,707
You full-on fawn over yourself
every chance you get.

287
00:19:28,342 --> 00:19:29,342
Come on.

288
00:19:29,562 --> 00:19:30,582
Go take a shower.

289
00:19:31,022 --> 00:19:33,222
We have something to take care of today.

290
00:19:35,262 --> 00:19:37,782
I need to buy soy sauce from Tim's.

291
00:19:38,822 --> 00:19:39,822
It's 'Toy's.'

292
00:19:40,022 --> 00:19:41,422
Right, my bad.

293
00:19:50,842 --> 00:19:54,482
(How were you guys last night?)

294
00:19:55,532 --> 00:19:56,752
Last night...

295
00:19:58,722 --> 00:19:59,722
Yeah...

296
00:20:02,912 --> 00:20:04,362
What the hell happened last night?

297
00:20:11,432 --> 00:20:13,012
Would you like to try our new recipe?

298
00:20:21,832 --> 00:20:22,922
Are you talking to me?

299
00:20:23,232 --> 00:20:25,462
Well, there are only two of us here.

300
00:20:31,962 --> 00:20:33,142
It's just that

301
00:20:33,502 --> 00:20:35,422
I made a new recipe.

302
00:20:35,822 --> 00:20:37,902
If it's not too much to ask,

303
00:20:38,442 --> 00:20:39,582
would you taste it for me?

304
00:20:50,313 --> 00:20:51,313
Mm!

305
00:20:51,982 --> 00:20:53,182
That's pretty good.

306
00:20:53,362 --> 00:20:55,275
The taste is quite well-balanced.

307
00:20:55,542 --> 00:20:57,102
What did you put in it?

308
00:20:57,518 --> 00:20:58,438
Some MSG.

309
00:20:58,483 --> 00:20:59,483
What?

310
00:21:00,662 --> 00:21:01,662
Just kidding.

311
00:21:02,102 --> 00:21:03,782
It's just our special fermented fruits.

312
00:21:05,962 --> 00:21:06,962
Well, well,

313
00:21:08,742 --> 00:21:09,982
I see that you've got jokes.

314
00:21:10,233 --> 00:21:11,265
Of course.

315
00:21:15,662 --> 00:21:17,022
(How were you guys last night?)

316
00:21:17,062 --> 00:21:19,572
All good. Nothing's wrong.

317
00:22:00,062 --> 00:22:01,302
Thank you for wearing it.

318
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:04,382
If I could cover myself
with the hotel's blanket, I would.

319
00:22:07,782 --> 00:22:09,702
Also, we're going out of town now.

320
00:22:09,882 --> 00:22:11,602
You didn't tell me
we would travel this far.

321
00:22:12,302 --> 00:22:13,822
For me,

322
00:22:14,322 --> 00:22:15,472
even if I had to travel

323
00:22:15,681 --> 00:22:17,542
to the horizon with you,

324
00:22:17,982 --> 00:22:19,542
I'd gladly do it.

325
00:22:20,302 --> 00:22:21,502
But not for me!

326
00:22:23,182 --> 00:22:25,742
Hey, I could even report you
to the police for kidnapping me!

327
00:22:27,062 --> 00:22:28,582
Are you gonna call the police on me?

328
00:22:28,902 --> 00:22:29,902
Yes.

329
00:22:32,132 --> 00:22:33,222
How cruel...

330
00:22:35,342 --> 00:22:36,462
But it's all good.

331
00:22:37,622 --> 00:22:39,382
Even if the police come to arrest me,

332
00:22:39,682 --> 00:22:41,282
they would only have custody of my body.

333
00:22:41,641 --> 00:22:42,641
Fu, what are you doing?

334
00:22:43,342 --> 00:22:45,192
Since my whole heart...

335
00:22:45,802 --> 00:22:47,022
is with you already.

336
00:22:50,862 --> 00:22:52,982
Fu, you're always talking nonsense.

337
00:22:53,842 --> 00:22:54,842
I'm out.

338
00:22:58,742 --> 00:23:01,462
Guess he must be really hungry,

339
00:23:01,982 --> 00:23:03,142
if he rushes off like that...

340
00:23:05,282 --> 00:23:06,312
Moo-Moo,

341
00:23:06,380 --> 00:23:07,550
wait for me!

342
00:23:12,982 --> 00:23:16,462
There's nothing
but Moo-Moo's favorite food on this table.

343
00:23:17,182 --> 00:23:19,622
It's all for you and no one else.

344
00:23:22,422 --> 00:23:23,422
Thank you.

345
00:23:26,702 --> 00:23:28,222
Is there anything else you want?

346
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:30,510
Tell me, and I'll get it for you.

347
00:23:32,902 --> 00:23:34,022
I wanna know,

348
00:23:34,262 --> 00:23:36,262
if I wanted deep-fried whale meat,

349
00:23:36,802 --> 00:23:38,102
would you get it for me?

350
00:23:40,182 --> 00:23:41,302
Deep-fried whale meat...

351
00:23:43,394 --> 00:23:44,394
What are you doing?

352
00:23:45,502 --> 00:23:46,502
It's really windy here.

353
00:23:48,362 --> 00:23:49,362
I...

354
00:23:49,822 --> 00:23:51,322
am going to find...

355
00:23:51,362 --> 00:23:53,002
a whale-hunting trip
to catch one for you.

356
00:23:53,232 --> 00:23:55,262
You wanna have
deep-fried whale meat, don't you?

357
00:23:55,862 --> 00:23:56,862
I was being sarcastic!

358
00:23:57,232 --> 00:23:58,232
Oh...

359
00:23:58,432 --> 00:23:59,942
And I was genuinely looking for it...

360
00:24:06,102 --> 00:24:07,942
Didn't you say
there was only my favorite food?

361
00:24:08,122 --> 00:24:09,122
How is this clear soup

362
00:24:09,242 --> 00:24:10,462
my favorite?

363
00:24:13,422 --> 00:24:15,182
Well, I have a sensitive stomach,

364
00:24:15,502 --> 00:24:16,742
though I have a strong heart.

365
00:24:18,822 --> 00:24:20,382
So much so that...

366
00:24:20,442 --> 00:24:23,402
it keeps beating and beating only for you.

367
00:24:27,792 --> 00:24:29,192
I'm hungry. Let's just eat.

368
00:24:30,542 --> 00:24:31,542
Flustered, huh?

369
00:24:31,662 --> 00:24:33,372
Come on, I'll help you with the food.

370
00:24:49,463 --> 00:24:51,023
Even dogs have a sweetheart,

371
00:24:53,047 --> 00:24:54,797
so when will you have my heart?

372
00:24:59,392 --> 00:25:00,392
Fu,

373
00:25:00,622 --> 00:25:01,622
seriously,

374
00:25:01,902 --> 00:25:03,862
can you act like a normal person

375
00:25:04,087 --> 00:25:05,927
and not bombard me
with all these pickup lines?

376
00:25:06,582 --> 00:25:07,782
I think it's better that way.

377
00:25:16,192 --> 00:25:17,272
Is it that if I act normal,

378
00:25:18,582 --> 00:25:19,622
he will be into me?

379
00:25:31,102 --> 00:25:32,102
Fu,

380
00:25:32,462 --> 00:25:33,462
be honest with me,

381
00:25:33,662 --> 00:25:35,222
did you plan to take me here for a meal

382
00:25:35,782 --> 00:25:37,022
or a trip?

383
00:25:37,222 --> 00:25:38,482
I...

384
00:25:40,382 --> 00:25:41,702
took you here to spend the night.

385
00:25:42,782 --> 00:25:43,782
Huh?!

386
00:25:44,142 --> 00:25:45,142
What did you say?!

387
00:25:45,382 --> 00:25:46,382
Spend the night?!

388
00:25:49,502 --> 00:25:50,182
I...

389
00:25:50,262 --> 00:25:52,602
already booked a nice hotel for us.

390
00:25:52,822 --> 00:25:54,222
But I didn't even pack any clothes!

391
00:25:55,012 --> 00:25:56,012
Mm... about that,

392
00:25:56,042 --> 00:25:57,238
I can just take you to buy some.

393
00:25:57,262 --> 00:25:58,902
I didn't even pack my essentials, either!

394
00:25:58,982 --> 00:26:00,422
I can take you to buy those, too.

395
00:26:00,502 --> 00:26:01,542
Are you serious right now?

396
00:26:04,742 --> 00:26:05,742
Just kidding!

397
00:26:06,382 --> 00:26:07,502
I was just playing with you.

398
00:26:08,382 --> 00:26:09,382
Playing?

399
00:26:09,902 --> 00:26:12,102
I really thought
I was going to have to call my family.

400
00:26:13,902 --> 00:26:14,902
Or do you...

401
00:26:15,242 --> 00:26:16,882
actually want to spend the night with me?

402
00:26:17,159 --> 00:26:19,761
- In all honesty, I could...
- Nope.

403
00:26:20,702 --> 00:26:21,862
Last night was enough.

404
00:26:23,982 --> 00:26:25,222
You're right.

405
00:26:25,722 --> 00:26:27,062
Last night,

406
00:26:27,542 --> 00:26:28,102
it truly was...

407
00:26:28,282 --> 00:26:30,862
a night spent between two of us.

408
00:26:32,302 --> 00:26:33,502
But this time,

409
00:26:34,262 --> 00:26:35,902
my Moo-Moo won't be intoxicated.

410
00:26:53,576 --> 00:26:54,696
How do Gen Zers do this?

411
00:26:55,992 --> 00:26:56,992
Like this?

412
00:27:00,862 --> 00:27:01,662
You're old.

413
00:27:01,742 --> 00:27:02,122
Huh?

414
00:27:02,142 --> 00:27:04,872
You're trying so hard to be a Gen Zer.
- But how do you guys do it?

415
00:27:05,262 --> 00:27:06,372
How do Gen Zers do it?

416
00:27:09,462 --> 00:27:10,582
Wow...

417
00:27:10,622 --> 00:27:11,782
Moo-Moo!

418
00:27:31,582 --> 00:27:32,902
My homework today,

419
00:27:34,350 --> 00:27:35,598
I'll leave it to you, Little Chicken.

420
00:27:35,622 --> 00:27:37,962
It's your homework, so do it yourself.
Why make me do it?

421
00:27:39,102 --> 00:27:40,142
Aren't you smart?

422
00:27:41,462 --> 00:27:43,222
Can't you do
this one little homework for me?

423
00:27:43,862 --> 00:27:45,142
If I do your homework,

424
00:27:45,362 --> 00:27:47,062
would you be able to do your exam?

425
00:27:47,702 --> 00:27:48,902
Jeez...

426
00:27:49,352 --> 00:27:50,452
The exam is one thing.

427
00:27:51,482 --> 00:27:52,482
This is just homework.

428
00:27:52,882 --> 00:27:53,882
It's not relevant.

429
00:27:54,192 --> 00:27:55,282
How can it not be?

430
00:27:59,142 --> 00:28:00,622
Just stop arguing and do it

431
00:28:01,222 --> 00:28:02,262
if you don't want trouble.

432
00:28:11,302 --> 00:28:12,782
Come on, guys. Let's eat.

433
00:28:14,062 --> 00:28:16,542
When will I be free from this monster?

434
00:28:37,535 --> 00:28:38,535
Moo,

435
00:28:39,982 --> 00:28:41,982
I ordered some food for your parents.

436
00:28:42,542 --> 00:28:43,302
We're good.

437
00:28:43,462 --> 00:28:45,062
You can give the food to your employees.

438
00:28:45,622 --> 00:28:46,862
There's no one home.

439
00:28:46,902 --> 00:28:48,062
They come home at odd hours.

440
00:28:48,702 --> 00:28:49,982
It's gonna go bad if we keep it.

441
00:28:50,582 --> 00:28:53,142
You can put it in the freezer
for when everyone comes home.

442
00:28:53,662 --> 00:28:55,062
It's freshly made,

443
00:28:55,342 --> 00:28:56,622
so it's not gonna go bad easily.

444
00:28:58,758 --> 00:29:00,598
Then, I'll just take the desserts.

445
00:29:00,964 --> 00:29:02,844
As for the rest,
just give it to your employees,

446
00:29:03,067 --> 00:29:04,307
so that it doesn't go to waste.

447
00:29:04,696 --> 00:29:05,456
But...

448
00:29:05,490 --> 00:29:07,670
It's meant for you.

449
00:29:08,448 --> 00:29:10,382
Can't you take it?

450
00:29:10,422 --> 00:29:11,422
Fu!

451
00:29:12,102 --> 00:29:13,462
I said, I'm not taking it!

452
00:29:14,182 --> 00:29:15,702
Why do you always keep pestering me?

453
00:29:16,702 --> 00:29:18,572
Didn't you say
you weren't gonna cross the line

454
00:29:18,606 --> 00:29:19,676
without my permission?

455
00:29:19,802 --> 00:29:21,062
What you're doing now

456
00:29:21,462 --> 00:29:22,998
- is even worse than crossing the line.
- Moo...

457
00:29:23,022 --> 00:29:24,022
I'm just...

458
00:29:24,342 --> 00:29:24,942
Fu, listen to me carefully.

459
00:29:25,142 --> 00:29:26,222
I'll be straight with you.

460
00:29:27,382 --> 00:29:28,542
Stop hitting on me.

461
00:30:16,822 --> 00:30:18,682
Didn't you say
you weren't gonna cross the line

462
00:30:18,722 --> 00:30:19,942
without my permission?

463
00:30:20,851 --> 00:30:22,151
What you're doing now

464
00:30:22,422 --> 00:30:23,902
is even worse than crossing the line.

465
00:30:27,262 --> 00:30:28,262
Mr. Fu.

466
00:30:28,702 --> 00:30:29,442
So...

467
00:30:29,482 --> 00:30:31,982
We are currently
accepting internship applications.

468
00:30:32,762 --> 00:30:33,692
There have been... uh...

469
00:30:33,712 --> 00:30:35,402
quite a lot of them submitted.

470
00:30:35,442 --> 00:30:37,442
So I brought them here
for you to make a selection.

471
00:30:38,222 --> 00:30:39,222
Alright.

472
00:30:39,902 --> 00:30:40,942
I'll be sure to make one.

473
00:30:43,842 --> 00:30:44,842
Mr. Fu?

474
00:30:44,932 --> 00:30:45,622
Yes?

475
00:30:45,903 --> 00:30:47,683
Thank you for dinner.

476
00:30:48,162 --> 00:30:49,762
The staff said it was scrumptious

477
00:30:49,802 --> 00:30:51,742
and asked me to thank you.

478
00:30:52,662 --> 00:30:53,662
Alright.

479
00:30:53,962 --> 00:30:56,232
It's nice that everyone likes it.

480
00:30:57,222 --> 00:30:57,812
Oh...

481
00:30:58,232 --> 00:31:00,082
Alright, if you'll excuse me.

482
00:32:18,596 --> 00:32:22,582
Moo, Moo, Moo, Moo-Moo,
Moo, Moo, Moo, Moo-Moo Jelly

483
00:32:22,622 --> 00:32:25,852
Nice and chewy, sweet and playful

484
00:32:25,932 --> 00:32:29,862
The goodness that everyone enjoys

485
00:32:29,902 --> 00:32:34,362
Moo-Moo-Moo! Moo, Moo, Moo, Moo, Moo-Moo,
Moo, Moo, Moo, Moo-Moo Jelly

486
00:32:34,422 --> 00:32:39,082
The goodness that your loved one
is waiting to chew, Moo-Moo Jelly

487
00:32:41,142 --> 00:32:42,622
Jelly!

488
00:32:43,002 --> 00:32:44,022
That was...

489
00:32:44,193 --> 00:32:46,033
the ad for Moo-Moo's favorite candy!

490
00:32:49,357 --> 00:32:50,597
Are my ancestors...

491
00:32:50,631 --> 00:32:52,091
sending me a sign...

492
00:32:52,202 --> 00:32:53,622
to always stay hopeful?

493
00:32:57,162 --> 00:32:58,162
That's right.

494
00:32:58,962 --> 00:33:00,022
Since...

495
00:33:00,262 --> 00:33:01,702
I'm this handsome,

496
00:33:01,963 --> 00:33:02,963
cool,

497
00:33:03,422 --> 00:33:04,582
well-educated,

498
00:33:04,933 --> 00:33:05,933
with a car,

499
00:33:06,043 --> 00:33:07,323
a phone that can take photos.

500
00:33:07,752 --> 00:33:10,212
My utterly perfect, flawless self

501
00:33:11,062 --> 00:33:12,862
can belong to no one,

502
00:33:13,322 --> 00:33:14,322
except...

503
00:33:15,162 --> 00:33:19,382
my Moo-Moo!!

504
00:33:23,102 --> 00:33:24,102
I got it.

505
00:33:25,352 --> 00:33:26,512
No matter what,

506
00:33:26,862 --> 00:33:29,462
I'm never gonna give up on Moo!

507
00:33:31,332 --> 00:33:32,332
Tee!

508
00:33:33,102 --> 00:33:35,382
I will never give up on Moo again!

509
00:33:38,104 --> 00:33:39,104
I...

510
00:33:39,183 --> 00:33:40,643
will tell him I love him

511
00:33:41,082 --> 00:33:42,902
until he accepts me.

512
00:33:45,622 --> 00:33:47,182
I was really worried earlier,

513
00:33:47,502 --> 00:33:48,742
seeing how sad you looked.

514
00:33:48,982 --> 00:33:50,382
That's why I'm keeping you company.

515
00:33:50,956 --> 00:33:52,716
But judging from your look now...

516
00:33:53,132 --> 00:33:54,972
does this mean
you're back to your normal self?

517
00:33:55,702 --> 00:33:56,702
Yes.

518
00:33:56,963 --> 00:33:57,963
I...

519
00:33:58,282 --> 00:34:01,782
am back to normal!!

520
00:34:12,742 --> 00:34:13,742
Fu!

521
00:34:17,302 --> 00:34:20,132
Thank you
for the companionship fee, anyway.

522
00:34:27,182 --> 00:34:28,222
Companionship fee, huh?

523
00:34:42,247 --> 00:34:43,727
Bro, you just stopped without a word.

524
00:34:44,557 --> 00:34:46,117
Who told you to come to the hotel, Tee?

525
00:34:46,508 --> 00:34:47,628
I didn't pay you to be here.

526
00:34:49,149 --> 00:34:51,389
- But don't you want a wingman?
- Wingman...

527
00:34:51,797 --> 00:34:53,477
I'm here to teach you how to win Moo over.

528
00:34:53,677 --> 00:34:55,317
Just 2,000 baht per trick.

529
00:34:55,591 --> 00:34:56,677
2,000...

530
00:34:58,217 --> 00:34:59,237
Tee!

531
00:34:59,367 --> 00:35:00,647
Are you addicted to video games?

532
00:35:01,217 --> 00:35:02,417
Why do you need so much money?

533
00:35:02,591 --> 00:35:03,671
You wouldn't know.

534
00:35:03,777 --> 00:35:04,537
These days,

535
00:35:04,557 --> 00:35:06,477
you need to pay for the good stuff.

536
00:35:09,837 --> 00:35:11,677
Hello, Mr. Fu, Tee.

537
00:35:11,997 --> 00:35:12,757
Hello.

538
00:35:12,827 --> 00:35:13,827
Long time no see.

539
00:35:14,637 --> 00:35:16,037
You'll see me more often, then,

540
00:35:16,331 --> 00:35:17,831
because Fu really needs me.

541
00:35:18,817 --> 00:35:20,197
How adorable of you two.

542
00:35:20,717 --> 00:35:21,477
Jang,

543
00:35:21,617 --> 00:35:23,115
would you like to take Tee under your care?

544
00:35:23,139 --> 00:35:24,559
He's bleeding me dry!

545
00:35:25,237 --> 00:35:26,417
Right, Mr. Fu,

546
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:28,517
there's an intern who starts today.

547
00:35:28,677 --> 00:35:29,447
Uh...

548
00:35:29,617 --> 00:35:31,197
I haven't seen the documents inside.

549
00:35:31,437 --> 00:35:32,497
Oh, is that so?

550
00:35:33,107 --> 00:35:34,517
It's just...

551
00:35:44,377 --> 00:35:46,277
Hello, Mr. Fu.

552
00:35:47,727 --> 00:35:48,887
I'm Moo-Moo,

553
00:35:49,542 --> 00:35:51,982
a new intern at Golden Peony Hotel.

554
00:35:52,837 --> 00:35:54,157
Please take care of me.

555
00:35:56,477 --> 00:35:59,677
